WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:20.000
Tristan Andizalder, re-toned by George Gibson, copyright, black cat publishing.

00:30.000 --> 00:35.000
Part one, the minstrel.

00:35.000 --> 00:43.000
One cold winter evening, King Arthur and his knights were sitting at the round table in the castle of Camelot.

00:43.000 --> 00:47.000
Suddenly, a tall young man came into the great hall.

00:47.000 --> 00:57.000
He had dark hair and dark sad eyes. His clothes were old but clean. He had a harp under his arm.

00:57.000 --> 00:59.000
Welcome to Camelot, young man.

00:59.000 --> 01:01.000
Said King Arthur.

01:01.000 --> 01:03.000
Are you a minstrel?

01:03.000 --> 01:05.000
Yes, Your Majesty. I am.

01:05.000 --> 01:06.000
Said the young man.

01:06.000 --> 01:07.000
Where are you from?

01:07.000 --> 01:09.000
Asked King Arthur.

01:09.000 --> 01:10.000
I'm from Cornwall.

01:10.000 --> 01:12.000
Answer the minstrel.

01:12.000 --> 01:13.000
Well.

01:13.000 --> 01:14.000
Said King Arthur.

01:14.000 --> 01:21.000
We like minstrels and their stories. Tell us a good story about brave knights and lovely ladies.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
Do you know the story of Sir Tristan of Leones?

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
Asked one of the knights.

01:26.000 --> 01:27.000
Yes, I do.

01:27.000 --> 01:29.000
Answer the minstrel.

01:29.000 --> 01:34.000
Sir Tristan is a brave knight but his story is very sad.

01:34.000 --> 01:36.000
Sit down and tell us.

01:36.000 --> 01:43.000
Said King Arthur. Everyone in the hall was interested in the story of Sir Tristan of Leones.

01:43.000 --> 01:48.000
The minstrel sat on a stool and started telling his story to the king and his knights.

01:48.000 --> 01:53.000
Sometimes he spoke and sometimes he sang and played his harp.

01:53.000 --> 01:56.000
This is the story he told.

01:56.000 --> 02:01.000
For many years there were wars between Cornwall and Ireland.

02:01.000 --> 02:06.000
The Irish often sailed across the sea to Cornwall and attacked it.

02:06.000 --> 02:10.000
There were terrible battles and many people died.

02:10.000 --> 02:16.000
King Mark of Cornwall wanted peace but the Irish did not.

02:16.000 --> 02:18.000
He did not know what to do.

02:18.000 --> 02:23.000
One day he asked his cousin, King Rivelin of Leones, for help.

02:23.000 --> 02:28.000
Help me fight the Irish and you can marry my beautiful sister.

02:28.000 --> 02:31.000
Said King Mark to his cousin.

02:31.000 --> 02:33.000
The Irish and my enemies too.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.000
Said King Rivelin.

02:35.000 --> 02:41.000
I'll help you fight them. Together we can win and I'll marry your beautiful sister.

02:41.000 --> 02:47.000
King Rivelin and King Mark fought together and won the war against the Irish.

02:47.000 --> 02:53.000
King Rivelin married King Mark's sister and they returned to his castle in Leones.

02:53.000 --> 03:01.000
They loved each other and were very happy together but their happiness did not continue for long.

03:01.000 --> 03:05.000
A year later King Rivelin was killed in battle.

03:05.000 --> 03:12.000
At the same time the queen had a son but she died soon after.

03:12.000 --> 03:16.000
Before dying she called her servant Ruel.

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
Ruel I'm dying.

03:18.000 --> 03:21.000
Said the young beautiful queen.

03:21.000 --> 03:24.000
Take my child and call him Tristan.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
His name means sadness.

03:26.000 --> 03:29.000
It comes from the French word Trist.

03:29.000 --> 03:32.000
Look after him and love him like a son.

03:32.000 --> 03:36.000
And when he is a man he must go and meet my brother.

03:36.000 --> 03:40.000
King Mark of Cornwall. He will help him.

03:40.000 --> 03:45.000
Ruel and his wife loved Little Tristan and they looked after him.

03:45.000 --> 03:48.000
He became a strong brave boy.

03:48.000 --> 03:53.000
He learned to use a sword, a spear and to ride a horse.

03:53.000 --> 03:57.000
He also learned to play the harp and speak other languages.

03:57.000 --> 04:05.000
When Tristan became a man he left Leones and went to Cornwall to meet his uncle King Mark.

04:05.000 --> 04:08.000
The king lived in a big castle in Tintagel.

04:08.000 --> 04:14.000
Tristan entered the great hall of the castle and saw his uncle for the first time.

04:15.000 --> 04:19.000
Your Majesty, I'm your nephew Tristan from Leones.

04:19.000 --> 04:24.000
My nephew? Tristan. My sister's son.

04:24.000 --> 04:28.000
Said King Mark, looking at the tall young man.

04:28.000 --> 04:33.000
Welcome to Tintagel. This is your new home.

04:33.000 --> 04:36.000
I'm very happy you're here.

04:36.000 --> 04:42.000
My knights and I will teach you many things and you'll become a great knight.

04:42.000 --> 04:45.000
Everyone welcomed Tristan to the castle.

04:45.000 --> 04:50.000
He was happy with his uncle who loved him like a son.

04:50.000 --> 04:54.000
He became a famous knight and fought in many battles.

04:54.000 --> 04:59.000
The people of Cornwall knew about his great courage and liked him.

04:59.000 --> 05:06.000
But some of the knights and nobles were jealous of him because he was King Mark's favorite knight.

05:07.000 --> 05:12.000
One day Sir Mohalt from Ireland came to Tintagel Castle.

05:12.000 --> 05:18.000
He was a gigantic man with a dark face and strong hands.

05:18.000 --> 05:21.000
King Gurman of Ireland sent me here.

05:21.000 --> 05:23.000
He said in a loud voice.

05:23.000 --> 05:26.000
He wants a tribute from you King Mark.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
A tribute?

05:28.000 --> 05:30.000
Said King Mark, surprised?

05:30.000 --> 05:32.000
Yes, a tribute.

05:32.000 --> 05:35.000
Said Sir Mohalt.

05:35.000 --> 05:41.000
If you send a tribute, King Gurman won't attack Cornwall.

05:41.000 --> 05:43.000
What is the tribute?

05:43.000 --> 05:44.000
asked King Mark.

05:44.000 --> 05:49.000
You must send him thirteen noble boys who will become his servants.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.000
What?

05:50.000 --> 05:52.000
cried King Mark.

05:52.000 --> 05:56.000
Thirty of our noble boys. This is terrible.

05:56.000 --> 05:59.000
You must do what King Gurman wants.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.000
Said Sir Mohalt.

06:01.000 --> 06:03.000
Or one of your knights can fight me.

06:03.000 --> 06:07.000
If your knight wins, you don't have to send a tribute to the king.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.000
But no one will fight me.

06:09.000 --> 06:12.000
I'm the strongest knight in the world.

06:12.000 --> 06:14.000
And everyone's afraid of me.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.000
Everyone was silent.

06:16.000 --> 06:20.000
But Tristan's face was red with anger.

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
I will fight you Sir Mohalt.

06:22.000 --> 06:23.000
Said Tristan.

06:23.000 --> 06:25.000
I'm not afraid of you.

06:25.000 --> 06:29.000
Everyone was surprised and looked at Tristan.

06:29.000 --> 06:34.000
No Tristan. Don't fight him. He's too big and strong.

06:34.000 --> 06:35.000
Said King Mark.

06:35.000 --> 06:38.000
You can't win. He'll kill you.

06:38.000 --> 06:41.000
No Uncle Mark. Said Tristan.

06:41.000 --> 06:46.000
I'm a knight of Cornwall and I must fight him.

06:46.000 --> 06:51.000
Sir Mohalt looked at the young man in front of him and started laughing.

06:51.000 --> 06:56.000
Tristan was much shorter and thinner than the Irish giant.

06:56.000 --> 07:00.000
I'll meet you in a week on a small island opposite the castle.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.000
Said Sir Mohalt.

07:02.000 --> 07:05.000
Come alone early in the morning.

07:05.000 --> 07:11.000
I'll be there, said Tristan, looking at Sir Mohalt's cold eyes.

07:15.000 --> 07:18.000
Part two. Sir Mohalt.

07:18.000 --> 07:26.000
A week later Sir Mohalt came to the island early in the morning.

07:26.000 --> 07:28.000
He pulled his boat onto the beach.

07:28.000 --> 07:33.000
Then Tristan came to the island, but he pushed his boat away.

07:33.000 --> 07:36.000
Why did you push your boat away?

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
Asked Sir Mohalt.

07:38.000 --> 07:41.000
You'll need it when you decide to run away from me.

07:41.000 --> 07:45.000
Tristan looked at him bravely and said,

07:45.000 --> 07:49.000
I won't run away because I'm not afraid of you.

07:49.000 --> 07:54.000
Remember, only one man will leave this island alive.

07:54.000 --> 07:58.000
Sir Mohalt laughed and raised his big sword.

07:58.000 --> 08:02.000
Tristan did the same and they started fighting.

08:02.000 --> 08:05.000
Tristan was young and light and he moved quickly.

08:05.000 --> 08:11.000
Sir Mohalt was slow and heavy, but he was very strong.

08:11.000 --> 08:16.000
Tristan jumped here and there and soon Sir Mohalt was tired,

08:16.000 --> 08:18.000
but he continued fighting.

08:18.000 --> 08:21.000
The fight went on for many hours.

08:21.000 --> 08:26.000
Suddenly Sir Mohalt wounded Tristan's leg with his big sword.

08:26.000 --> 08:29.000
Test poison on my sword.

08:29.000 --> 08:32.000
Said Sir Mohalt, laughing.

08:32.000 --> 08:36.000
If you don't find someone to cure your wound, you'll be very ill.

08:36.000 --> 08:39.000
And only a few people in the world can cure it.

08:39.000 --> 08:44.000
Tristan was very angry and raised his heavy sword.

08:44.000 --> 08:48.000
He cut through Sir Mohalt's helmet and wounded his head.

08:48.000 --> 08:54.000
A small piece of Tristan's sword broke and remained in Sir Mohalt's head.

08:54.000 --> 08:58.000
The Irish giant fell to the ground.

08:58.000 --> 09:01.000
He was almost dead.

09:01.000 --> 09:06.000
That evening, some of Sir Mohalt's men came to the island.

09:06.000 --> 09:10.000
They were surprised to see him on the ground, wounded.

09:10.000 --> 09:16.000
They put him on their boat and sailed back to Ireland where he died.

09:16.000 --> 09:24.000
His sister was the queen of Ireland and she was very sad because she loved her brother.

09:24.000 --> 09:33.000
She took the small piece of sword from Sir Mohalt's head and put it in a small blue box in her room.

09:33.000 --> 09:36.000
One day, I'll find the man who killed my brother.

09:36.000 --> 09:38.000
She thought.

09:38.000 --> 09:44.000
Tristan returned to Tintajal Castle, but his wound made him very ill.

09:44.000 --> 09:50.000
King Mark called the best doctors of Cornwall, but they could not help him.

09:50.000 --> 09:54.000
Tristan must go to Ireland to cure his wound.

09:54.000 --> 09:56.000
Said an old doctor.

09:56.000 --> 09:59.000
Because the poison comes from there.

09:59.000 --> 10:05.000
The queen of Ireland knows everything about poisons and herbs.

10:05.000 --> 10:08.000
She can help him.

10:08.000 --> 10:12.000
Then Tristan must go to Ireland immediately.

10:12.000 --> 10:13.000
Said King Mark.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.000
Get a ship ready.

10:15.000 --> 10:22.000
Tristan went to Ireland dressed as a minstrel and called himself Tantris.

10:22.000 --> 10:26.000
He did not want anyone to know that he was Sir Tristan.

10:26.000 --> 10:32.000
He played the harp and sang beautifully and the Irish liked his songs.

10:32.000 --> 10:39.000
One day, King Gurman heard about the minstrel and called him to his castle.

10:39.000 --> 10:46.000
King Gurman and his queen had only one child, a lovely daughter called Isolda.

10:47.000 --> 10:56.000
She was the most beautiful girl in the world with long blonde hair, blue eyes and a lovely smile.

10:56.000 --> 10:59.000
Everyone talked about her beauty.

10:59.000 --> 11:05.000
The king wanted Isolda to play the harp, but there were no good teachers in Ireland.

11:05.000 --> 11:10.000
Tantris entered the great hall of the castle with his harp.

11:10.000 --> 11:13.000
He walked slowly because his leg hurt.

11:13.000 --> 11:16.000
Are you the famous minstrel Tantris?

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
asked King Gurman.

11:18.000 --> 11:22.000
Yes, I'm the minstrel, said Tristan.

11:22.000 --> 11:24.000
What's wrong with your leg?

11:24.000 --> 11:25.000
asked the king.

11:25.000 --> 11:30.000
I wounded it during a terrible battle, said Tristan.

11:30.000 --> 11:34.000
People say you play the harp beautifully, said King Gurman.

11:34.000 --> 11:37.000
Play something for me.

11:37.000 --> 11:43.000
Tristan played the harp and sang a lovely song and the king was pleased.

11:43.000 --> 11:47.000
Can you teach my daughter Isolda to play the harp?

11:47.000 --> 11:49.000
asked the king.

11:49.000 --> 11:53.000
Of course I can, said Tristan happily.

11:53.000 --> 11:56.000
Very well, said the king.

11:56.000 --> 12:02.000
The queen will cure your wound with her special herbs and you will teach Isolda to play the harp.

12:02.000 --> 12:04.000
You can live here at the castle.

12:04.000 --> 12:09.000
Thank you, Your Majesty, said Tristan, smiling.

12:09.000 --> 12:14.000
I'm glad everyone thinks I'm a minstrel, thought Tristan.

12:14.000 --> 12:20.000
Now my leg will get better and I'll soon go back to Cornwall.

12:20.000 --> 12:23.000
Tristan's leg slowly got better.

12:23.000 --> 12:27.000
Every morning he taught Isolda to play the harp and sing.

12:27.000 --> 12:32.000
Isolda learned quickly and the king was very happy.

12:32.000 --> 12:41.000
During the harp lessons Tristan often thought Isolda is very beautiful.

12:43.000 --> 12:48.000
Part 3, The Dragon

12:48.000 --> 12:55.000
Tristan stayed in Ireland at King Gurman's Castle and taught Isolda to play the harp and sing.

12:55.000 --> 13:01.000
He and Isolda became good friends and often laughed and talked together.

13:01.000 --> 13:05.000
Isolda became a good singer and harp player.

13:05.000 --> 13:10.000
She played the harp and sang songs for her parents and other nobles.

13:10.000 --> 13:14.000
After a year Tristan returned to Cornwall.

13:14.000 --> 13:18.000
King Mark was very happy to see his nephew.

13:18.000 --> 13:24.000
Every day Tristan told his uncle about Isolda's great beauty.

13:25.000 --> 13:31.000
Isolda is the most beautiful girl in the world and she is gentle and kind.

13:31.000 --> 13:37.000
Her hair is the color of gold and her eyes are the color of the sea.

13:37.000 --> 13:42.000
She plays the harp well and sings with a sweet voice.

13:42.000 --> 13:53.000
King Mark listened to Tristan and said, Isolda is King Gurman's only daughter and she is beautiful and kind.

13:53.000 --> 13:58.000
If I marry her there will be peace between our two countries.

13:58.000 --> 14:05.000
The king's knights and nobles agreed with him but there was one problem.

14:05.000 --> 14:11.000
We agree with you said one noble but how can you marry Princess Isolda?

14:11.000 --> 14:16.000
The king and queen of Ireland hate us because Sir Mohalt was killed here.

14:16.000 --> 14:20.000
He's right said another noble.

14:20.000 --> 14:27.000
King Mark was silent for a moment and then said, I want to marry Isolda.

14:27.000 --> 14:33.000
I'll have the most beautiful wife in the world and there will be peace between our countries.

14:33.000 --> 14:36.000
We must find a way.

14:36.000 --> 14:41.000
He looked at Tristan but he didn't say anything.

14:41.000 --> 14:45.000
Tristan knew what his uncle wanted.

14:45.000 --> 14:50.000
Uncle Mark said Tristan, I know this is a dangerous adventure.

14:50.000 --> 14:55.000
When the queen of Ireland discovers who I am she'll be very angry.

14:55.000 --> 15:01.000
She hates the knight who killed her brother Mohalt but I'm not afraid.

15:01.000 --> 15:06.000
I'll bring Isolda to you Uncle Mark and you can marry her.

15:06.000 --> 15:11.000
Your brave and loyal Tristan said King Mark.

15:11.000 --> 15:14.000
Be very careful.

15:14.000 --> 15:19.000
Tristan sailed to Ireland on a small ship with 30 men.

15:19.000 --> 15:23.000
They arrived in Ireland on a stormy night.

15:23.000 --> 15:27.000
I must think of a plan, thought Tristan.

15:27.000 --> 15:31.000
I must bring Isolda to King Mark.

15:31.000 --> 15:36.000
At that time a terrible green dragon lived in Ireland.

15:36.000 --> 15:42.000
It killed a lot of people and burned houses and trees with its fire.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.000
No one could kill it.

15:44.000 --> 15:49.000
King Gurman was worried and didn't know what to do.

15:49.000 --> 15:52.000
One day he said to his nobles,

15:52.000 --> 16:01.000
The man who kills the terrible green dragon will marry my lovely daughter Isolda.

16:01.000 --> 16:07.000
Everyone in Ireland was talking about this and Tristan heard about it too.

16:07.000 --> 16:11.000
He was excited because he wanted to kill the dragon.

16:11.000 --> 16:17.000
He had a heavy sword, a long lance and a big shield.

16:17.000 --> 16:24.000
He rode to the valley of the dragon and saw the dead bodies of other knights who tried to kill it.

16:24.000 --> 16:27.000
Suddenly Tristan saw the angry dragon.

16:27.000 --> 16:32.000
It was a terrible green monster with long white teeth,

16:32.000 --> 16:36.000
Angry red eyes and a long tail.

16:36.000 --> 16:40.000
Fire and smoke came out of its mouth.

16:40.000 --> 16:44.000
What an ugly creature, thought Tristan.

16:44.000 --> 16:48.000
He attacked the dragon with his lance and sword.

16:48.000 --> 16:54.000
They fought for more than an hour and in the end Tristan killed it with his long lance.

16:54.000 --> 16:59.000
The dragon's last breath was hot and poisonous.

16:59.000 --> 17:02.000
Tristan soon felt very bad.

17:02.000 --> 17:06.000
He went to the dead dragon and opened its big mouth.

17:06.000 --> 17:11.000
Then he cut out its tongue and put it in his bag.

17:11.000 --> 17:16.000
This tongue will show that I killed the dragon, he thought.

17:16.000 --> 17:21.000
The poison made him ill and he fell to the ground.

17:21.000 --> 17:29.000
Later that day one of the king's nobles called Seniscale came to the valley of the dragon.

17:29.000 --> 17:33.000
He liked his older very much and he wanted to marry her.

17:33.000 --> 17:37.000
But he was a coward and was afraid of the dragon.

17:37.000 --> 17:41.000
When Seniscale saw the dead dragon he thought.

17:41.000 --> 17:43.000
This is wonderful.

17:43.000 --> 17:46.000
Someone already killed the dragon.

17:46.000 --> 17:51.000
I can tell the king I killed it and then I can marry his own.

17:51.000 --> 17:57.000
But first I must cut off the dead dragon's head to show the king.

17:57.000 --> 18:01.000
He cut off the head and took it to the king.

18:01.000 --> 18:03.000
You mad justy?

18:03.000 --> 18:04.000
He said.

18:04.000 --> 18:08.000
I killed the green dragon. Look, here is its head.

18:08.000 --> 18:12.000
Now I can marry your daughter. Princess is old.

18:12.000 --> 18:18.000
The king knew Seniscale was a coward and he did not believe him.

18:18.000 --> 18:22.000
But the head of the dragon was in front of him.

18:22.000 --> 18:27.000
When his older heard this she started crying and could not stop.

18:27.000 --> 18:29.000
What's wrong is oldy?

18:29.000 --> 18:31.000
Asked the queen.

18:31.000 --> 18:32.000
Mother.

18:32.000 --> 18:33.000
Said his older crying.

18:33.000 --> 18:38.000
I don't like Seniscale and I don't want to marry him.

18:38.000 --> 18:40.000
Don't cry my dear.

18:40.000 --> 18:41.000
Said the queen.

18:41.000 --> 18:44.000
I don't believe Seniscale killed the dragon.

18:44.000 --> 18:46.000
Come with me quickly.

18:46.000 --> 18:51.000
That evening they went to the valley and found the dead dragon and Tristan on the ground.

18:51.000 --> 18:52.000
Look.

18:52.000 --> 18:53.000
Cried his older.

18:53.000 --> 18:56.000
It's tantrous, the minstrel.

18:56.000 --> 18:58.000
But he's dressed like a knight.

18:58.000 --> 19:00.000
I don't understand.

19:00.000 --> 19:05.000
Tristan heard his older sweet voice and slowly moved his head.

19:05.000 --> 19:07.000
Are you tantrous?

19:07.000 --> 19:08.000
Asked the queen.

19:08.000 --> 19:13.000
He opened his eyes and said, yes, I am.

19:13.000 --> 19:15.000
Why are you in Ireland?

19:15.000 --> 19:17.000
Asked the queen.

19:17.000 --> 19:21.000
I came to Ireland with some merchants, he said.

19:21.000 --> 19:23.000
Did you kill the dragon?

19:23.000 --> 19:25.000
Asked the queen.

19:25.000 --> 19:28.000
I knew there was a terrible dragon in your country.

19:28.000 --> 19:30.000
And I decided to kill it.

19:30.000 --> 19:31.000
Said Tristan.

19:31.000 --> 19:35.000
The queen listened and smiled.

19:35.000 --> 19:39.000
Tantrous, you did a great thing and helped our country.

19:39.000 --> 19:41.000
The king will be very pleased.

19:41.000 --> 19:45.000
But you aren't well because the dragon poisoned you.

19:45.000 --> 19:54.000
Come with us to the castle and I'll cure you again with my herbs.

19:54.000 --> 19:58.000
For Seniscan.

19:58.000 --> 20:05.000
Once again, the Irish queen cured Tristan with her magic herbs and his older helped her.

20:05.000 --> 20:11.000
After a week he got better and went to the Great Hall to see King Gurman.

20:11.000 --> 20:16.000
There was a big dinner in honour of Seniscan who wanted to marry his older.

20:16.000 --> 20:23.000
King Gurman, the queen, his older knights, nobles and their ladies were sitting at a

20:23.000 --> 20:25.000
long table.

20:25.000 --> 20:31.000
Seniscan talked to his friends and told them about his fight with the dragon.

20:31.000 --> 20:33.000
It was a long, terrible fight.

20:33.000 --> 20:35.000
He said loudly.

20:35.000 --> 20:37.000
But I was never afraid.

20:37.000 --> 20:42.000
I got very near to the green monster and looked at his red eyes.

20:42.000 --> 20:47.000
I saw his long, white teeth and felt his heart breath in my face.

20:47.000 --> 20:52.000
I knew I had to kill him and in the end I dead.

20:52.000 --> 20:54.000
Then I cut his head off.

20:54.000 --> 20:59.000
The king was silent, but the queen was not.

20:59.000 --> 21:02.000
She looked at Seniscan and said,

21:02.000 --> 21:05.000
You didn't kill the dragon.

21:05.000 --> 21:09.000
You found the dead dragon and cut his head off.

21:09.000 --> 21:10.000
What?

21:10.000 --> 21:12.000
Said Seniscan angrily.

21:12.000 --> 21:16.000
I killed the dragon with my lance after a long fight.

21:16.000 --> 21:19.000
Said Tristan, getting up from his chair.

21:19.000 --> 21:23.000
You're a liar and a coward.

21:23.000 --> 21:26.000
Seniscan got up from his chair and said,

