40:31.000 --> 40:34.000
Her name was Isola too.

40:34.000 --> 40:36.000
Isola of the white hands.

40:36.000 --> 40:41.000
She was a pretty young girl and Tristan liked her.

40:42.000 --> 40:46.000
Why do I like Isola of the white hands?

40:46.000 --> 40:47.000
He thought.

40:47.000 --> 40:51.000
Do I like her smile or her voice?

40:51.000 --> 40:54.000
Do I like her lovely white hands?

40:54.000 --> 40:57.000
Or do I like her name?

40:57.000 --> 40:59.000
Do I love her?

40:59.000 --> 41:02.000
Tristan could not answer these questions.

41:02.000 --> 41:05.000
But he decided to marry her.

41:05.000 --> 41:09.000
Isola of the white hands was a good loving wife.

41:09.000 --> 41:13.000
And Tristan was a kind, loyal husband.

41:13.000 --> 41:18.000
But he was not happy because he could not forget Queen Isola.

41:18.000 --> 41:22.000
She was his first and only love.

41:22.000 --> 41:27.000
Isola of the white hands knew this and she was jealous.

41:27.000 --> 41:31.000
Why can't Tristan love me like he loves her?

41:31.000 --> 41:32.000
She thought.

41:32.000 --> 41:37.000
One day Tristan fought in a battle to help his wife's brother, Cajedine.

41:37.000 --> 41:40.000
It was a long, terrible battle.

41:40.000 --> 41:43.000
And Tristan was wounded with a poisoned spear.

41:43.000 --> 41:46.000
His wound made him very ill.

41:46.000 --> 41:50.000
He could not walk and stayed in bed a long time.

41:50.000 --> 41:53.000
But he did not get better.

41:53.000 --> 41:55.000
He got worse.

41:55.000 --> 41:57.000
I'm very ill.

41:57.000 --> 41:59.000
Said Tristan to Cajedine.

41:59.000 --> 42:02.000
And I think I'm going to die soon.

42:02.000 --> 42:04.000
No Tristan.

42:04.000 --> 42:05.000
Said Cajedine.

42:05.000 --> 42:07.000
Don't say that.

42:07.000 --> 42:11.000
You helped me during the battle and now I want to help you.

42:11.000 --> 42:15.000
Tell me what I can do, my friend.

42:15.000 --> 42:22.000
Only Queen Isola of Cornwall can cure my wound because the spear was poisoned.

42:22.000 --> 42:24.000
Said Tristan weakly.

42:24.000 --> 42:29.000
She learned the secrets of the magic herbs from her mother.

42:29.000 --> 42:36.000
Then I'll sail to Tintagil immediately and ask Queen Isola to come here and cure you.

42:36.000 --> 42:37.000
Said Cajedine.

42:37.000 --> 42:40.000
Oh Cajedine, thank you.

42:40.000 --> 42:41.000
Said Tristan.

42:41.000 --> 42:48.000
If Isola comes with you, raise the white sail on your ship.

42:48.000 --> 42:53.000
But if she doesn't, then raise the black sail.

42:53.000 --> 42:54.000
Very well.

42:54.000 --> 42:56.000
Said Cajedine.

42:56.000 --> 42:58.000
I'm leaving this evening.

42:58.000 --> 43:02.000
Isola of the white hands heard this conversation.

43:02.000 --> 43:05.000
And she was angry and jealous.

43:05.000 --> 43:12.000
Cajedine sailed to Cornwall and told King Mark and Queen Isola about Tristan's wound.

43:12.000 --> 43:16.000
I must go and cure his wound with my magic herbs.

43:16.000 --> 43:18.000
Said Queen Isola.

43:18.000 --> 43:23.000
I'm the only person who can save his life.

43:23.000 --> 43:27.000
King Mark looked at his wife and said...

43:27.000 --> 43:31.000
Time is helping me to forget many things.

43:31.000 --> 43:34.000
I think I can trust you now, Isola.

43:34.000 --> 43:37.000
Go and cure Tristan's wound.

43:37.000 --> 43:39.000
Yes, my king.

43:39.000 --> 43:42.000
Said Queen Isola quietly.

43:42.000 --> 43:45.000
You can trust me.

43:45.000 --> 43:52.000
Isola left Cornwall with Cajedine the same day with some bottles of herbs and potions.

43:52.000 --> 43:58.000
When the ship arrived near Tristan's castle, Cajedine raised the white sail.

43:58.000 --> 44:04.000
Tristan was very weak and could not get up from bed and look out of the window.

44:04.000 --> 44:08.000
He called his wife and said...

44:08.000 --> 44:11.000
Go and look out of the window.

44:11.000 --> 44:15.000
Cajedine's ship will be here soon.

44:15.000 --> 44:17.000
Can you see it?

44:17.000 --> 44:24.000
Isola of the white hands went to the window and saw Cajedine's ship with its big white sail.

44:24.000 --> 44:25.000
Oh no.

44:25.000 --> 44:26.000
She thought...

44:26.000 --> 44:28.000
The sail's white.

44:28.000 --> 44:30.000
Queen Isola is here.

44:30.000 --> 44:32.000
She was very jealous.

44:32.000 --> 44:33.000
Yes, Tristan.

44:33.000 --> 44:36.000
Said Isola of the white hands.

44:36.000 --> 44:38.000
Cajedine's ship is here.

44:38.000 --> 44:41.000
What color is the sail?

44:41.000 --> 44:43.000
Asked Tristan weakly.

44:43.000 --> 44:46.000
The sail is... black.

44:46.000 --> 44:49.000
Aunts it is older of the white hands.

44:49.000 --> 44:51.000
Oh, no.

44:51.000 --> 44:54.000
Isola my love.

44:54.000 --> 44:56.000
Said Tristan, sadly.

44:56.000 --> 44:59.000
You didn't come to me.

44:59.000 --> 45:03.000
I won't see your beautiful face again.

45:03.000 --> 45:05.000
Oh, dearest Isola.

45:05.000 --> 45:08.000
Dearest Isola.

45:08.000 --> 45:12.000
And then he closed his eyes and died.

45:12.000 --> 45:17.000
Queen Isola came to Tristan's room and saw his dead body.

45:17.000 --> 45:22.000
She sat down on the bed and looked at him for the last time.

45:22.000 --> 45:27.000
Her sadness was very great and her heart broke.

45:27.000 --> 45:30.000
She died next to him.

45:30.000 --> 45:32.000
What did I do?

45:32.000 --> 45:36.000
My terrible jealousy killed them both.

45:36.000 --> 45:38.000
Said Isola of the white hands.

45:38.000 --> 45:41.000
And she was very sorry.

45:41.000 --> 45:44.000
But it was too late.

45:44.000 --> 45:48.000
Tristan and his older were buried together in one grave.

45:48.000 --> 45:54.000
And over the grave, Isola of the white hands planted two rose trees.

45:54.000 --> 45:57.000
A red one and a white one.

45:57.000 --> 46:01.000
They grew together with red and white roses.

46:01.000 --> 46:08.000
And this is the end of the great love story of Sir Tristan of Leoness

46:08.000 --> 46:12.000
Queen Isola of Cornwall.

